# Basics of Github
- What is Github?
    * A hosting platform for Git repos
    * Git is a VCS, but Github is a web hosted platform that hosts Git repos that people can collaborate on
    * Github is the largest such platform, followed by Gitlab
- Cloning
    * Cloning is how we create a local version of a cloud hosted repo on our machine (such as a repo hosted on Github)
    * git clone [link]
    